# Snowflake Connection Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and replace with your actual credentials
# Get these from: Profile Icon → Account → View Account Details

# === OPTION A: Browser Authentication (Recommended - More Secure) ===
# Get these from your Snowflake profile config:
SNOWFLAKE_USER=YOUR_USERNAME                 
SNOWFLAKE_ACCOUNT=YOUR_ACCOUNT_ID            
SNOWFLAKE_AUTHENTICATOR=externalbrowser      
SNOWFLAKE_ROLE=YOUR_ROLE                     
SNOWFLAKE_WAREHOUSE=YOUR_WAREHOUSE           
SNOWFLAKE_DATABASE=YOUR_DATABASE             
SNOWFLAKE_SCHEMA=YOUR_SCHEMA                 

# === OPTION B: Password Authentication (Traditional) ===
# Uncomment and use these instead if you prefer username/password:
# SNOWFLAKE_USER=your_username_here
# SNOWFLAKE_PASSWORD=your_password_here
# SNOWFLAKE_ACCOUNT=your_account_identifier_here
# SNOWFLAKE_WAREHOUSE=your_warehouse_name_here
# SNOWFLAKE_DATABASE=your_database_name_here
# SNOWFLAKE_SCHEMA=your_schema_name_here

# Tips:
# - Browser auth is more secure (no stored passwords)
# - Use exact case for USER (e.g., FULLNAME not fullname)
# - Account ID format: ORGNAME-ACCOUNTNAME or ACCOUNT.REGION
# - DATABASE/SCHEMA are optional - you can change context in queries